"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819123?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》</p></figcaption></figure></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/pepper-and-salt-11ee1595</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/pepper-and-salt-11ee1595<category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>社论</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>仅标题内容</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>社论</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>仅标题内容</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Here Lies Love’ Review: David Byrne’s Dictator Disco Party]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>这部百老汇音乐剧由 Talking Heads 主唱和 Fatboy Slim 配乐，描绘了菲律宾前第一夫人伊梅尔达·马科斯动荡、奢华的生活<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590096021884730284"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820110?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">阿莉尔·雅各布斯 (Arielle Jacobs) 和《爱在此》的演员们</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：比利·布斯塔曼特、马修·墨菲和埃文·齐默尔曼</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590096021884730284"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"><span class="author" itemprop="name">查尔斯·伊舍伍德</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日晚上 9:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/here-lies-love-review-david-byrnes-dictator-disco-party-a84cc46d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>臭名昭著的菲律宾前第一夫人伊梅尔达·马科斯似乎不太可能成为百老汇音乐剧的女主角。但伊娃·庇隆也是如此，她与这个人物有很多共同点，而根据她的生活改编的音乐剧也成为了一种国际现象。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4></h4><p><strong>这里蕴藏着爱</strong></p><p><em>百老汇剧院，1681 Broadway，纽约，49-199 美元，212-239-6200</em></p></div></div><p>无论如何，追溯马科斯动荡人生轨迹的《爱在此》与传统的百老汇演出完全不同。该剧由 Talking Heads 主唱 David Byrne 构思，并负责作词作曲（后者与 Fatboy Slim 合作），该剧于 10 年前首次在百老汇外上演，是一场令人心旷神怡的迪斯科舞会混合体（舞会中充满了巨大的镜面球，悬停在整个表演过程中）和纪录片。</p><p>百老汇剧院已被改造得面目全非：管弦乐队部分的座位已被拆除，以便许多观众站着（或跳舞）观看演出，而伊梅尔达的生活则像一场盛会一样展开，无论是在剧院原来的舞台还是礼堂周围的平台上。中央的那一个本身就在跳舞，以各种配置旋转，要求舞台监督挥舞着发光的警棍将站立的观众赶出轨道——就像机场工作人员引导飞机进出登机口一样。 （我应该指出，座位也是一种选择；早在 2013 年，我就选择了这些座位，并且可以保证那些这样做的人不会感到被排除在外。）</p><p>不可抗拒的配乐与百老汇的其他音乐一样，用一个疲惫的短语来说，在这种情况下就是简单的事实。伯恩先生一直是一位音乐喜鹊，在这里他提供了一系列令人眼花缭乱的不拘一格的歌曲。这些歌曲有旋律优美的歌谣，探讨了伊梅尔达从菲律宾一个省级岛屿上的贫困到她与一位政治新星的童话般的婚姻。当阿莉尔·雅各布斯（Arielle Jacobs）饰演的伊梅尔达（Imelda）（由阿莉尔·雅各布斯（Arielle Jacobs）饰演）光芒四射、充满诱惑，和她的丈夫费迪南德（何塞·拉纳（Jose Llana），散发着冷静的野心）登上总统宝座并成为受人爱戴的公众人物后，派对正式开始，强劲的低音线涌动，观众被鼓励加入到快乐的混战中，甚至还被要求编舞。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820115?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">何塞·拉纳及其公司</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：比利·布斯塔曼特、马修·墨菲和埃文·齐默尔曼</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>伯恩先生在歌词中借鉴了伊梅尔达的真实话语（以及剧中其他人物的话语），这表明这种润肤且芳香浓郁的药膏中可能存在一只苍蝇。伊梅尔达是一位极其精明的公众表演者，她利用自己不可否认的魅力、美丽和受欢迎程度，为马科斯家族日益贪婪和野蛮掠夺国家财富提供豪华掩护，以填补他们自己的银行账户——当然还有他们的鞋柜（尽管伯恩先生明智地避免提及伊梅尔达过度公开的鞋类迷恋）。</p><p>因此，《爱在此》中的伊梅尔达是按照她塑造和培养的形象塑造的；我们几乎看不到装饰华丽的外观下面的情况。即使伊梅尔达去监狱探望马科斯家族的宿敌参议员尼诺·阿基诺（康拉德·里卡莫拉饰）——他们因他直言不讳的反对而将他扔进监狱——她给人的印象更多的是同情而不是无情。 （尽管这在一定程度上可以用她与伊梅尔达早期情人尼诺的不寻常历史来解释。）即使该剧开始更深入地探索这对夫妇的可怕掠夺行为，伊梅尔达仍然是一个迷人的、显然毫无头绪的人物，不知何故与马科斯政权给菲律宾造成的恐怖区别开来。</p><p>这部音乐剧首次制作时，因近乎圣徒传而受到批评，将伊梅尔达变成了闪亮的流行歌星——她有时对着闪闪发光的麦克风唱歌。当然，这部由亚历克斯·廷伯斯（Alex Timbers）执导的华而不实、光鲜亮丽的作品（他的标志是光鲜亮丽；参见《红磨坊！》），在90分钟的片长中，大部分时间都在鼓励观众通过玫瑰色眼镜观看“塔克洛班玫瑰”（伊梅尔达被称为“塔克洛班玫瑰”）——塔克洛班是她长大的城市。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="1049" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820101?width=700&amp;height=1049" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">康拉德·里卡莫拉和雅各布斯女士</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：比利·布斯塔曼特、马修·墨菲和埃文·齐默尔曼</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>更多剧院评论</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-saviour-review-irish-repertory-marie-mullen-c110ed97?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">《救世主》评论：疑惑闯入喜悦</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 13 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-whos-tommy-and-another-marriage-reviews-pinball-wizards-coupled-writers-1912765e?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">《谁是汤米》和《另一场婚姻》评论：弹球奇才、情侣作家</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 6 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hamlet-review-shakespeare-in-the-park-with-a-modern-twist-15c9229e?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">《哈姆雷特》评论：现代风格的公园莎士比亚</a><span class="date">2023 年 6 月 29 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/once-upon-a-one-more-time-review-princesses-with-britney-spears-e1e61468?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">《童话镇》评论：与（布兰妮）斯皮尔斯的公主</a><span class="date">2023 年 6 月 22 日</span></li></ul></div></div><p>然而，这个版本在鼓励观众为勇敢的伊梅尔达的崛起欢呼和揭露表面背后的残酷真相之间感觉更加平衡。当节目开始将坐飞机的伊梅尔达与剧院周围的视频屏幕上闪现的令人震惊的统计数据并列时，这是故意的，让人迷失方向，其中包括伊梅尔达在她最喜欢的文化项目上花费的巨额资金。</p><p>当我们听到歌曲《1081号令》时，这首歌详细描述了马科斯为镇压反对政权的民众起义而采取的严厉措施，包括实施戒严令，庆祝活动已经结束，旋转的迪斯科球已经停止旋转，我们跳舞的脚现在牢牢地踩在了地上。</p><p> 《爱在此》最引人注目的地方在于，当我们目睹阿基诺流放归来后在机场被暗杀时，它如何巧妙地从对伊梅尔达崛起的庆祝甚至感伤的呈现转向不可避免的谴责。莉亚·萨隆加 (Lea Salonga) 在《西贡小姐》上映 30 多年后，以出色的嗓音饰演阿基诺的母亲，主持他的葬礼（尽管萨隆加女士的表演只持续到 8 月 13 日）。</p><p>该剧在快节奏的结局中恢复了活力，重演了令人耳目一新的主打歌。但当粉红色的纸飘带洒落在观众身上时，您在抓起一把作为纪念品之前可能会三思而后行。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> -先生。伊舍伍德是《华尔街日报》的戏剧评论家。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 01:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/here-lies-love-review-david-byrnes-dictator-disco-party-a84cc46d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/here-lies-love-review-david-byrnes-dictator-disco-party-a84cc46d<category>艺术评论</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>音乐</category><category>音乐剧</category><category>剧院</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>艺术回顾</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>音乐</category><category>音乐剧</category><category>剧院</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Nobody in Hollywood’ Like Xi Jinping]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>特朗普说，中国领导人“聪明、才华横溢，一切都很完美”。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590100093353339422"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590100093353339422"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 6:51 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-xi-jinping-cedar-rapids-town-hall-sean-hannity-15bfe172"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821267?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 2017 年，中国国家主席习近平和唐纳德·特朗普总统。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：nicolas asfouri/法新社/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>尽管特朗普总统自 2016 年当选以来说了很多令人惊讶的事情，但他仍然有能力让人惊讶。周二，肖恩·汉尼提 (Sean Hannity) 在爱荷华州锡达拉皮兹参加福克斯新闻市政厅的录制时，听到特朗普对中国领导人习近平给出了奇怪的最高评价，令人震惊。</p><p> “想想习主席，”特朗普对人群说。 “中央铸造。才华横溢的家伙。你知道，当我说他很聪明时，每个人都会说，“哦，那太糟糕了”。 。 。嗯，他用铁腕统治着14亿人民。聪明，聪明，一切都很完美。好莱坞没有人能像这个人一样。”</p><p>一切都完美吗？对于一位前总统和2024年候选人来说，谈论一个美国对手是多么令人困惑，美国对手压制了香港的自由，系统性地镇压维吾尔族，掩盖了全球冠状病毒大流行的潜在根源，而且如果时机到来，他可能计划通过入侵台湾来发动战争。</p><p>特朗普过去曾对习近平和其他人（包括俄罗斯总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">弗拉基米尔·普京）</a>说过类似的话，他在周二做出了解释。 “他们聪明、坚韧，而且拥有大量核武器，”他说。 “拥有良好的关系——我试图向假新闻解释这一点——这是一件好事，而不是一件坏事。”</p><p>他有一个观点，即他的政府的行动有时比他的，呃，外交言论更强硬。在奥巴马总统拒绝后，特朗普总统向乌克兰发射了“标枪”导弹。不过，特朗普先生没有理由这样说话。认识到对手是危险的，因为他很聪明是一回事。但好莱坞不会让观众忘记谁是反派，谁是主角。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=142AA7D8-F7CE-46CC-8C97-37E8E30612D1&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fdonald-trump-xi-jinping-cedar-rapids-town-hall-sean-hannity-15bfe172&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">仙境：受中国和沙特阿拉伯的启发，拜登团队对美国产业政策的愿景是政府明确主导的；其他人都跟着。图片：美联社/法新社/盖蒂图片社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 22:51:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-xi-jinping-cedar-rapids-town-hall-sean-hannity-15bfe172</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/donald-trump-xi-jinping-cedar-rapids-town-hall-sean-hannity-15bfe172<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>习近平</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Parable of F-16s for Ukraine]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>一个案例研究为什么基辅的反攻进展缓慢、痛苦。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590096222420801484"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590096222420801484"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 6:44 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-offensive-weapons-russia-f-16s-biden-administration-mark-milley-263cf9ec"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821235?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 6月23日，一架美国空军F-16战斗机在德国雅格尔空军基地起飞</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：丹尼尔·莱因哈特/DPA/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>美国官员向媒体窃窃私语，称乌克兰人在欧洲数十年来最血腥的战斗中表现不佳。这是多么不体面的举动：拜登的支持者保留了乌克兰击败俄罗斯入侵所需的重火力，然后哀叹基辅没有足够快地夺回足够的领土。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>乌克兰人正在努力突破俄罗斯戒备森严的防御。马克·米利将军周二表示：“这与第一次世界大战时的战壕线并不完全相连，但也与第一次世界大战没有什么不同——许多复杂的雷区、龙牙、铁丝网和战壕。”乌克兰装备被俄罗斯地雷炸毁，基辅军队需要更多帮助来清除爆炸物。</p><p>攻势仍处于初期阶段，乌克兰还没有投入西方训练的大部分部队。但美国官员在未透露姓名的情况下告诉媒体，乌克兰人并不擅长联合作战，即协调使用坦克、步兵、空中力量和其他资产。</p><p>但西方军队不会在不控制天空的情况下发动这次进攻。乌克兰军队很容易受到俄罗斯的攻击，而且他们缺乏空中力量来支持地面部队并在不冒巨大损失的情况下进攻俄罗斯的阵地。</p><p> F-16战斗机将是一个很大的进步。正如退役空军中将布鲁斯·赖特 (Bruce Wright) <a href="https://www.airandspaceforces.com/airpower-is-the-key-to-victory-in-ukraine/" target="_blank" class="icon none">在 2 月份所写的</a>那样，俄罗斯地对空导弹发射场对于 F-16 飞行员来说“可能是利润丰厚的目标”。远程精确武器可以帮助“摧毁俄罗斯边境附近的防空系统，并摧毁俄罗斯坦克、火炮和乌克兰东部的阵地”。</p><p>西方盟国预计下个月开始训练乌克兰飞行员驾驶 F-16。但事实是乌克兰现在本来可以拥有这样的飞行员并飞行。美国从一开始就知道乌克兰苏联时代的喷气机队没有能力与俄罗斯规模更大、更先进的部队竞争。尽管如此，乌克兰仍然巧妙地使用了美国的反辐射导弹，躲避了俄罗斯的防空系统，从而获得了一些空中优势。</p><p>这些页面建议<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/arming-for-the-next-fight-in-ukraine-russia-war-biden-administration-pentagon-11649972971?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在 2022 年 4 月</a>将乌克兰飞行员纳入美国飞行训练计划。然而，拜登政府甚至在是否转让一些摇摇欲坠的波兰 MiG-29 方面也犹豫不决。今年 2 月，拜登总统表示乌克兰“不需要”F-16，但<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/f-16-jets-for-ukraine-joe-biden-russia-7f3606c8" target="_blank" class="icon none">三个月</a>后却决定美国将支持盟军培训乌克兰飞行员的努力。</p><p>唉，不要以为美国有意愿在喷气式飞机上跟进。参谋长联席会议主席米利将军周二提醒记者，这些飞机价格昂贵。他说，一支大型机队需要数年时间——“数年时间来培训飞行员，数年时间进行维护和维持，数年时间来获得实现这一目标的财政支持。你说的是比已经产生的资金多出数十亿美元的资金。”</p><p>然而，提供 F-16 的成本远低于乌克兰的失败，而乌克兰的失败让美国更深地陷入了欧洲的问题之中。 F-16 在世界各地的军队中服役，拥有广泛的承包商基础，可以帮助建立维护支持。与美国向乌克兰捐赠的每一件武器一样——从坦克到爱国者防空系统再到希马尔大炮——拜登政府表示，这些系统太复杂，无法提供给基辅，直到有一天这些问题突然被宣布可以解决。</p><p>这种犹豫不决的法案即将到期，悲剧是乌克兰人伤亡更多，反攻更加令人担忧。随着越来越多的美国人开始怀疑美国正在取得的成就，这种犹豫不决也削弱了国内的政治支持。拜登仍然可以断定，美国不希望乌克兰陷入漫长而丑陋的泥潭。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=52B0CFB0-0E03-4C90-9E19-A15E110CDD96&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fukraine-offensive-weapons-russia-f-16s-biden-administration-mark-milley-263cf9ec&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">回顾与展望：美国国税局特工加里·沙普利和约瑟夫·齐格勒在宣誓后表示，他们调查亨特·拜登的尝试面临着司法部前所未有的干预。司法部长梅里克·加兰和特拉华州联邦检察官大卫·韦斯会做出回应吗？图片：彭博新闻/盖蒂图片社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 22:44:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-offective-weapons-Russia-f-16s-biden-administration-mark-milley-263cf9ec</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-offective-weapons-Russia-f-16s-biden-administration-mark-milley-263cf9ec<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[A Spanish Lesson for Europe]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>人民党展示了中间派保守派如何获胜。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12705823021609713873204590085404251575626"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12705823021609713873204590085404251575626"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 6:43 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/spain-election-popular-party-alberto-nunez-feijoo-pedro-sanchez-cd045d78"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821238?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 7 月 20 日，西班牙右翼反对党人民党领袖阿尔贝托·努涅斯·费乔在马德里举行的竞选会议上发表讲话。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：pierre-philippe marcou/法新社/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>西班牙周日举行投票，这有望成为欧洲一场令人耳目一新的正常选举。民意调查显示，该国将对中左翼政府做出判断，因为他们因投票支持中右翼政党而对中左翼政府失去了信心。如今，这在欧洲来说是一个意外。</p><p>中左翼社会主义工人党总理佩德罗·桑切斯上任五年后，选民似乎准备抛弃他。不满情绪来自多个角落。</p><p>事实证明，桑切斯在新冠疫情期间实施的封锁措施——欧洲最严格的封锁措施之一——并不受许多人欢迎，而且西班牙的经济从疫情中复苏的速度也很缓慢。目前通胀率为 1.6%，低于欧洲其他地区，但物价水平仍远高于 2020 年初，且工资水平尚未跟上。失业率为12.7%。</p><p>桑切斯先生还跨越了西班牙政治中的几条文化红线。他在议会中与地区分离主义政党和共产党结成便利联盟，并煽动与佛朗哥独裁统治有关的争议。佛朗哥于 1975 年去世。</p><p>所有这一切都让阿尔贝托·努涅斯·费乔领导的中右翼人民党有机会在议会中赢得令人信服的多数席位。该党通过将促增长的经济政策和文化温和政策结合起来，将自己置于这样的境地，而文化温和政策曾经是政治右翼的面包和黄油。</p><p>虽然经济并不是竞选的主要焦点，但人民党试图与选民对话，对他们来说，经济低迷是其他不满情绪的背景。主题是通过税收改革和放松管制创造机会，鼓励投资并允许个人和企业保留更多收入。费乔先生并没有提出罗纳德·里根或玛格丽特·撒切尔那样的供应方大爆炸，但他提出的并不是左翼再分配的右翼版本。</p><p>人民党坚守在“文化战争”的前线，它认为那里存在广泛的联盟。这包括强调民族团结而不是地区分离主义，以及取消桑切斯在变性问题上的一些激进政策，同时忽视右翼对同性婚姻和公众认为已经解决的其他问题的抱怨。</p><p>这对其他地方的保守派来说是一个教训。费约先生并没有像英国保守党或德国安格拉·默克尔领导的基督教民主党那样在经济或文化问题上左倾。他也没有像许多所谓的国家保守派所主张的那样，在全面文化战争的另一个方向上摇摆得太远，这会疏远中间派选民。</p><p>如果人民党获胜，那将是因为它搭建了一个大帐篷，可以容纳自由市场中间派和一些在之前选举中转向更保守的 Vox 党的民族团结保守派。费乔先生可能仍需要与 Vox 组建联合政府，但凭借强大的多数票，他可以凭借强大的实力来实现这一目标。</p><p>如果欧洲中右翼政党能够以保守政策策略取得成功，同时仍能吸引中间派选民，那将是健康的发展。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=25232CEE-3316-437F-9EED-9F82FA7070FC&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fspain-election-popular-party-alberto-nunez-feijoo-pedro-sanchez-cd045d78&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">杂志社论报道：但共和党中的一些人不喜欢这些选秀权。图片：Getty Images/Zuma Press 综合：Mark Kelly<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 22:43:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/spain-election-popular-party-alberto-nunez-feijoo-pedro-sanchez-cd045d78</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/spain-election-popular-party-alberto-nunez-feijoo-pedro-sanchez-cd045d78<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>大众党</category><category>阿尔贝托·努涅斯·费乔</category><category>佩德罗·桑切斯</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Post-Pandemic Teaching Loss]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> “我们对老师的生锈和严谨表现得怎么样？”不好。&#39; <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590096413455870360"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590096413455870360"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 6:43 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/center-on-reinventing-public-education-report-teachers-education-pandemic-learning-loss-a28e7e7e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821240?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：Getty Images/iStockphoto</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>联邦政府向学校拨款 1900 亿美元，用于采取新冠病毒安全措施并帮助学生赶上进度，许多学校已将资金投入辅导或其他项目。那么为什么考试成绩仍然落后呢？一份新报告表明，教学损失正在加剧大流行性学习损失。</p><p>重塑公共教育中心的研究人员采访了五个公立特许学区和传统学区的领导层，他们表示，学校管理人员表示，“事实证明，他们的恢复计划几乎不可能成功实施，主要是由于人员配备和培训方面的挑战”。所有系统都表示课堂教学受到了影响，“这意味着改善日常教学必须成为他们的首要任务。”</p><p> <a href="https://crpe.org/pandemic-teaching-recovery-july-2023/" target="_blank" class="icon none">报告</a>中最令人沮丧的部分是学校领导对从“专业期望的侵蚀”到教师流动等各个方面的直接引用：</p><p> • “我们在留任奖金和‘请留下来’付款上花了很多钱。你还不如把钱烧掉，因为它没有兑现。人还是走了。人们拿着支票就走了。”</p><p> • “有很多老师[他们]又回到了. 。 。传统做法。更多的老师只是在教授内容，而孩子们却非常不投入。”</p><p> • “我们对老师的生疏和严谨表现得怎么样？不好。”</p><p> • “有 。 。 。很多，“我们刚刚度过这一天……” 。 。这就是我们正在做的一切。”</p><p> • “教师对课外专业学习的兴趣[尚未恢复。老师们真的就是不参加。”</p><p> • “我们在保持步伐方面仍面临一些挑战。尽管步伐已经被修改、修改、修改。”</p><p>远程教学和远程学习一样令人沮丧。去年的<a href="https://ies.ed.gov/schoolsurvey/spp/" target="_blank" class="icon none">一项联邦调查显示，</a>百分之三十七的公立学校的教师缺勤率“大幅增加”。大流行使课堂观察和协作暂停。报告称：“许多学区领导期望能够让学生跟上的‘学习加速’模式需要先进的教学策略，因此当许多教师需要帮助复习基础知识时，这种模式很难实现。”</p><p>哈佛大学教育政策研究中心 12 月的一份报告发现，学校常常很难找到教职员工，也很难找到最需要辅导和其他补充学习服务的学生。作者说：“学术干预的逻辑听起来很简单，但背后隐藏着一系列复杂的设计和实施决策。”</p><p>与此同时，并不是所有的新冠疫情资金都花在了学术帮助上。 The 74 网站的一份<a href="https://www.the74million.org/article/190b-later-reason-to-worry-relief-funds-wont-curb-covids-academic-crisis" target="_blank" class="icon none">新报告</a>发现，一些学区“投入了数百万美元用于主要的教室扩建、升级运动场以及与疫情无关的其他支出。”犹他州的一个系统花费了 86,000 美元在拉斯维加斯凯撒宫举办夏季教师会议。其他地区将新冠疫情资金用于日常开支，其中一个地区支付了一笔国家贷款。</p><p>学校停课是新冠疫情期间做出的最糟糕的决定之一，学业的恢复也没有如期实现。难怪家长们会在公立学校之外寻求帮助。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=B516DA74-BFDF-48DF-8837-7500103F43CF&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fcenter-on-reinventing-public-education-report-teachers-education-pandemic-learning-loss-a28e7e7e&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">在 2023 年 4 月 26 日的证词中，兰迪·温加滕 (Randi Weingarten) 详细介绍了美国教师联合会、拜登政府和疾病控制中心之间在 Covid-19 学校关闭政策方面的亲密关系。图片：美联社/Shutterstock/路透社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 22:43:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/center-on-reinventing-public-education-report-teachers-education-pandemic-learning-loss-a28e7e7e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/center-on-reinventing-public-education-report-teachers-education-pandemic-learning-loss-a28e7e7e<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>教育</category><category>学校</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>重塑公共教育中心</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>教育</category><category>学校</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Talent Strikes Back]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>好莱坞编剧和演员正在上演本世纪最大规模的劳工行动。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590099921346939914"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590099921346939914"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/peggy-noonan"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BS053_noonan_AM_20180912120458.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/peggy-noonan" itemprop="url" rel="author">佩吉·努南</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 5:31 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-talent-strikes-back-hollywood-union-writers-actors-tv-movie-industry-6bf4e49f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821142?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 7 月 18 日，导演兼编剧黛博拉·坎普梅尔在纽约走在纠察线上。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：MIKE SEGAR/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>我既不是娱乐记者，也不是行业资深人士，但我密切关注好莱坞的商业和文化，对这次罢工有不好的预感。我希望我是错的，但编剧和演员工会与电影电视制片人联盟之间的斗争在我看来似乎会持续很长时间并且是史诗般的。我们可以将其视为 21 世纪重要的劳工行动之一。</p><p>业内称，2021年影视直接创造就业岗位33.6万个，支持就业岗位240万人。年工资总额估计为 1,860 亿美元。它们构成了美国的主要出口产品。因此，罢工不仅具有经济意义，而且具有文化意义。无论您对其产品有何批评，我们都希望这个讲故事的行业能够继续下去。你希望它雇用那些正在努力、有成就的人，你希望它的艺术和一般艺术蓬勃发展，因为没有他们，我们就会变得不那么人性化，不那么完整。</p><p>上周，聪明人认为，美国演员工会-美国电视和广播艺术家联合会加入美国作家协会罢工将增加影响力并迫使事情得到解决。我的想法恰恰相反。美国演员工会-阿夫特拉 (SAG-Aftra) 的加入提高了所有赌注，激发了热情，并更加强调斗争的生存方面。巴里·迪勒（Barry Diller）是该行业真正的智者，他上周日在“面对国家”节目中分享了他的警报。 “当然，谁关心好莱坞？”他说。 “但这些情况可能会导致整个行业的绝对崩溃。”如果罢工持续到秋季，人们将取消流媒体订阅，因为“将没有节目”。也没有新的广播剧或喜剧。罢工时间越长，对美国主要工业的损害就越大。</p><p>我担心的是，冲突并不在于盈利公司的有能力的所有者和想要更大份额的工会成员之间。这不是 1960 年的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/F" class="company-name">福特</a>与装配线上的工人之间的较量，也不是回到过去，富裕的报纸老板与记者之间的较量。这不是安全与饥饿的问题。它看起来更像是失去视力的迷失者与感到真正悲伤的受屈者。</p><p>迷失的人是企业首席执行官、工作室和流媒体老板，当世界在 2020 年发生在每个人的脚下时，他们感到震惊。大流行加速了现有趋势，他们争先恐后地做出反应。影院上映是不可能的；流媒体就是一切；他们竞相推出新服务并在内容上花费数十亿美元，尽管事实证明到目前为止没有人知道如何在流媒体上可靠地赚钱。 （正如迪勒先生在 2021 年的支出狂潮中所说，“几年前， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="company-name">Netflix</a>就赢得了胜利。”）他们进行了高价的大型合并，让他们的公司背负了数百亿美元的债务。华尔街不喜欢这样，股市也随之波动。</p><p>他们现在正在努力把自己从深渊里挖出来。慈善光泽：当历史性瘟疫与技术革命发生碰撞时，他们竭尽全力。不那么慈善的读物：他们犯了一个又一个错误，现在将像他们花钱一样无创意地削减成本。当我们想到好莱坞时，我们不禁会想起老海盗萨姆·戈德温和杰克·华纳，他们以自己的强盗方式热爱电影。他们的继任者更像是某种超然抽象的金融主义兼并者，他们在公司内部移动，但直觉上对它们一无所知。不知何故，无论成功还是失败，他们的天文数字工资都在不断上涨。</p><p>反对他们的是受害人民、演员和作家。随着流媒体的兴起，他们的工作被剥夺了全额剩余报酬，这违反了传统和历史。他们看到了人工智能的本质：<em>我变成了死亡，工作的破坏者</em>。还有世界。还有言语。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>了解更多声明</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ai-artificial-intelligence-ukraine-war-russia-putin-china-brooke-astor-c6a9a1fa?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">夏日天空中的精灵</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 13 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/may-trump-soon-reach-his-waterloo-race-election-president-2024-candidate-campaign-97310a7f?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">愿特朗普很快抵达滑铁卢</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 6 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/what-will-prigozhins-rebellion-mean-russia-putin-wagner-group-war-ukraine-europe-893d0c3f?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">普里戈任的叛乱意味着什么？</a> <span class="date">2023 年 6 月 29 日</span></li></ul></div></div><p>老作家的房间里有十几个人，有福利，将被人工智能所取代，制片人将告诉人工智能，要在 1970 年的芝加哥创作一部谋杀悬疑小说，并且会这么做。然后，一位没有健康保险的人类作家将被召集来“让它变得更加破烂和人性化”。你可以说，“哦，那永远不会发生，没有机器可以做作家所做的事情——人类所具有的细微差别、微妙之处和敏感性。”但人工智能的能力每天都在增长。</p><p>这将使过去 40 年来最大的创意赤字变得更糟。很久以前，作家和演员从生活中学习他们的职业——生活在最浓重的生活中，在好莱坞之前从事过工作，常常知道自己的地位很低。他们把这种经验带到了好莱坞。他们到达时知道真实和普通的人类如何用语言表达自己，如何移动和思考。它充满活力，是民主的，并在一定程度上解释了 1930-90 年代好莱坞伟大的表演和写作。 （曾两度担任美国演员工会主席的罗纳德·里根认为，好莱坞的黄金时代是 1930 年代，那时有声电影开始流行，文字的声音就像一个奇迹，因此受到尊重。） 但到了某个时候，所有新作家和演员都来自媒体，而不是某个真正的美国或真实的世界。他们通过一生观看的电视节目和电影学会了如何思考和表达自己；他们的行动和写作都是基于他们在非现实生活中吸收的东西。它让一切变得不那么真实，而且每一代人的真实性都变得越来越薄弱。</p><p>人工智能不会缓解这个问题，反而会让问题变得更糟。它将以人工为食并复制它。</p><p>目前尚未进行正式谈判，也几乎没有明显的信任。上周四，当美国演员工会主席弗兰·德雷舍 (Fran Drescher) 带领演员们出发时，她的演讲非常激烈。 “我们是这里的受害者，”她说。 “我们正在成为一个非常贪婪的实体的受害者。我对那些与我们有业务往来的人对待我们的方式感到震惊。”早些时候，Deadline 援引一位未透露姓名的工作室高管的话说：“最终的结果是让事情拖延下去，直到工会成员开始失去他们的公寓和房子。”</p><p>我们不是劳工调解员，但一般建议是降低温度。双方有一个共同的目标：行业的永续发展。这只是一份为期三年的合同。双方都不必达到涅槃；虽然现实会自行解决，但朝着正确方向迈出的坚实步伐就是进步。会谈应该开始了。坐在餐桌旁不说话总比不在餐桌旁好。 （里根在 1960 年主持美国演员工会，这是美国演员工会和美国演员工会最后一次一起出去时，他曾观察到，在上厕所的休息时间里发生的突破比你想象的要多。） 演员们在台上应该反对风格，不要发表充满感情的长篇演讲，并且冷酷地讲事实。制作人，别肥了，别专横了。你的毛衣背心上拿着的那些大牌是吗？你甚至不知道。谦虚就是一切。</p><p>最终，制片人将不得不对人才采取更慷慨的分享最终财富的方式，并将其写在纸上。预测：如果他们继续强硬，他们不会成功地打破工会，但他们会让整个行业感到不满——如果这种情况持续那么久的话——并给他们自己的名字蒙上阴影。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=48E03FE9-F0A5-41FB-8532-879C1D176E1F&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fthe-talent-strikes-back-hollywood-union-writers-actors-tv-movie-industry-6bf4e49f&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">代表演员和编剧的电视和电影工会自 1960 年以来首次就 Netflix、Disney+ 和 Amazon Prime 等流媒体平台的更高薪酬等问题举行罢工。图片：祖马出版社/美联社/盖蒂图片社/路透社 综合：马克·凯利<span class="imageCredit">华尔街日报互动版</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div>]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 21:31:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-talent-strikes-back-hollywood-union-writers-actors-tv-movie-industry-6bf4e49f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-talent-strikes-back-hollywood-union-writers-actors-tv-movie-industry-6bf4e49f<author><![CDATA[Peggy Noonan]]></author><category>电影</category><category>电视</category><category>联盟</category><category>罢工</category><category>好莱坞</category><category>文化</category><category>电影</category><category>艾</category><category>演员</category><category>劳动争议</category><category>作家</category><category>劳工/人事</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>劳动争议</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>电影</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>劳动</category><category>人员</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>劳资纠纷</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>电影</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Son of a Critch’ Review: A Comic’s Chaotic Coming-of-Age]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> CW 剧集根据喜剧演员马克·克里奇 (Mark Critch) 的回忆录改编，将他在 20 世纪 80 年代纽芬兰的童年带入了混乱而尴尬的初中生活<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590097813126713670"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820053?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">本杰明·埃文·安斯沃斯和马尔科姆·麦克道威尔</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：狮门影业</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12136984570395233300204590097813126713670"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"><span class="author" itemprop="name">约翰·安德森</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 5:26 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/son-of-a-critch-review-a-comics-chaotic-coming-of-age-abb4ea14"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> <strong>《恶棍之子》</strong>可能是电视喜剧史上最尴尬的标题，但尴尬正是这部剧的精髓所在。改编自加拿大喜剧演员马克·克里奇的同名回忆录，作者是一个在 1986 年纽芬兰长大的过于理智的青少年，进入初中，成为一名书呆子，他的每一次互动都受到年长的自我的批评。想象一下，如果《美好岁月》由让·谢泼德 (Jean Shepherd) 撰写，并由朱迪·布鲁姆 (Judy Blume) 和亨特·S·汤普森 (Hunter S. Thompson) 提供额外对话。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4></h4><p><strong>克里奇之子</strong></p><p><em>周一，晚上 8 点，CW</em></p></div></div><p>然而，该剧的导演是克里奇先生，他与执行制片人蒂姆·麦考利夫共同创作了该剧，并饰演自己的父亲迈克。 Benjamin Evan Ainsworth (of the live-action “Pinocchio”) is the young Mark, who has all the credentials necessary to be bullied unmercifully as he begins a new term at a not-so-nearby Catholic school run by nuns who conform to all the stereotypes, but are funny nonetheless. “Feeling chatty?” barks Sister Rose ( Nora McLellan ), staring down Mark&#39;s new friend, the note-passing Ritchie ( Mark Rivera ). “Why don&#39;t you tell us the parts of the reproductive system?!” Sex ed never seemed so confrontational. The sisters are terrorists. So are the kids. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820057?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Mark Critch</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Project 10 Productions Inc. </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> More Television Reviews</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/stephen-curry-underrated-review-a-warriors-mettle-ce20721e?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Stephen Curry: Underrated&#39; Review: A Warrior&#39;s Mettle</a> <span class="date">July 20, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/black-sands-review-perilous-prospects-nordic-noir-b39e9aa8?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Black Sands&#39; Review: Perilous Prospects, Nordic Noir</a> <span class="date">July 18, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/superpowered-the-dc-story-review-max-imum-glorification-7d98deb0?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Superpowered: The DC Story&#39; Review: Max(imum) Glorification</a> <span class="date">July 18, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/goliath-review-how-wilt-chamberlain-changed-the-game-518350d4?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Goliath&#39; Review: How Wilt Chamberlain Changed the Game</a> <span class="date">July 13, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> On the most basic level, “Son of a Critch” is just fun, with crazy people. Mark shares a room with his grandfather, whom he calls Pop, played by a dryly hilarious Malcolm McDowell. Mr. McDowell seems to relish his role as the irascible elder who performs his morning ablutions with no regard for his grandson. (“Nothing gets you out of bed faster than being mooned by an octogenarian,” Mark recalls.) His father runs a radio station and seals his son&#39;s fate among his peers by sending him good luck over the airwaves, which are being picked up on the school bus. Mark&#39;s mother, Mary (Claire Rankin), has told her son quite plainly, as he headed off for his first day at a new school, that sure, the other children will bully you. Beat you up. Think you&#39;re strange. (“Strange?”) But just be yourself. (“Oh, don&#39;t do that,” warns his older brother, played by Colton Gobbo. )</p><p> Mark has no intention of being anybody else; if there&#39;s a novel twist to Mr. Critch&#39;s roman à clef, it is the self-awareness of its protagonist. The younger Critch knows he&#39;s surrounded by eccentrics. He is one himself.</p><p> Chief among Mark&#39;s antagonists are the siblings and habitual bullies known as Fox—the Fox in Mark&#39;s class is played by the very promising Sophia Powers, but she has two older brothers who are also called Fox and who take great glee in eating Mark&#39;s lunch, literally and figuratively. It is hard to imagine Mark and Fox not growing up and getting married. But that would be many laughs away from now.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> -先生。 Anderson is the Journal&#39;s TV critic.</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 21:26:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/son-of-a-critch-review-a-comics-chaotic-coming-of-age-abb4ea14</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/son-of-a-critch-review-a-comics-chaotic-coming-of-age-abb4ea14<category>艺术评论</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Civil Unrest</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>Society/Community</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>Social Issues</category><category>电视/广播</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>艺术回顾</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>civil unrest</category><category> national</category><category>公安</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>社会问题</category><category>电视</category><category>收音机</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pilobolus Review: The Dance-Theater Troupe’s ‘Big Five-Oh!’]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> The company celebrates at the Joyce Theater, where a decades-spanning mix of offerings demonstrates its signature athleticism and style <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590099910144336830"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="1131" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820675?width=860&amp;height=1131" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Pilobolus in &#39;Ballad&#39;</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Ben McKeown </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11277182998813654381604590099910144336830"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Robert Greskovic</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 20, 2023 5:26 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pilobolus-review-the-dance-theater-troupes-big-five-oh-69dc2f93"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> The current three-week season of Pilobolus at the Joyce Theater, through July 30, is billed as a celebration of its “Big Five-Oh!” even though the dance-theater group, now under the shared artistic directorship of Renée Jaworski and Matt Kent, was founded in 1971. It is wrapping up a golden anniversary tour that trailed into this year due to interruptions caused by the Covid-19 pandemic. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4></h4><p> <strong>Pilobolus</strong></p><p> <em>Joyce Theater, through July 30</em></p></div></div><p> Two mixed bills—arranged as Programs A and B, each with one intermission—make up the run of 11 works, spanning offerings from the troupe&#39;s first year to those created in 2023. Pilobolus, named for an active fungus found in the dung of grazing animals, originally was three men strong before evolving into a now-longstanding core group of four men and two women, with alternate performers on hand.</p><p> Of the two programs making up this season and that will alternate during the run&#39;s final week, B presents the stronger mix. Its first part concludes with “Untitled,” perhaps the group&#39;s most familiar and popular work.</p><p> Created and first performed in 1975 by Robby Barnett, Alison Chase, Martha Clarke, Moses Pendleton, Michael Tracy and Jonathan Wolken —arguably the group&#39;s most memorable sextet—the often witty movement and pantomime composition of intermittently surreal activities evoking a Victorian atmosphere prompts the theater&#39;s notice that “Tonight&#39;s performance contains nudity.” Both simulated and actual nakedness are at times part of the Pilobolus repertory, but none of these instances are salacious; one journalist early on likened this aspect of the group&#39;s aesthetic to skinny-dipping.</p><p> “On the Nature of Things,” a 2014 creation credited to 13 collaborators, opens Program B as succinct activity for three nearly nude performers: Nathaniel Buchsbaum, Quincy Ellis and Marlon Feliz at the performance I caught. Their mostly slow-motion movements occur on a kind of model stand where a lone woman and two men execute sculptural postures, accompanied by a selection of Vivaldi. Their poses suggest a blending of Eadweard Muybridge&#39;s stop-action photo studies with Nicolas Poussin&#39;s figure groupings.</p><p> “Branches” (2017, credited to 10 collaborators) on Program A is set to sound design by David Van Tiegham and presents the current company bathed in Thom Weaver&#39;s golden lighting and wearing Liz Prince&#39;s nude-look costuming. Its actions and interactions move from coy and cartoonish behavior to tableaus of glowing bodies that transform the performers&#39; physiques into impressive images of flora and fauna. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> More Dance Reviews</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/like-water-for-chocolate-review-an-overstuffed-ballet-5c74e2e5?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Like Water for Chocolate&#39; Review: An Overstuffed Ballet</a> <span class="date">June 28, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-york-city-ballet-review-balanchine-and-beyond-d98f57a9?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">New York City Ballet Review: Balanchine and Beyond</a> <span class="date">May 9, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/martha-graham-dance-company-in-its-founders-shadow-781038c7?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Martha Graham Dance Company: In Its Founder&#39;s Shadow</a> <span class="date">April 26, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/agua-review-pina-bauschs-brazilian-dance-spectacle-5e020dee?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Água&#39; Review: Pina Bausch&#39;s Brazilian Dance Spectacle</a> <span class="date">March 7, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> Program B&#39;s “Walklyndon” (1971, by Wolken, Lee Harris, Mr. Barnett and Mr. Pendleton) is the earliest work included here. Its vaudeville-like, slapstick collisions and acrobatic encounters for the full troupe as it strides through stage crossovers, in silence, consistently elicit laughter, chuckles as well as the odd groan from its audiences. Another effective oldie, “Solo From the &#39;Empty Suitor&#39;” (1980, by Mr. Tracy to a recording of Ben Webster&#39;s “Sweet Georgia Brown”), seen on Program A, presents a hapless fellow, Mr. Buchsbaum, as a silent-movie-style clown who finds himself walking on some log-like tubes as iffy as ice floes. Eventually, he ends up becoming trapped beneath a two-seat bench, much to the audience&#39;s amusement.</p><p> Three New York premieres are included on these programs; two on A and one on B. None stand out.</p><p> The miscellaneous athletic maneuverings of Program A&#39;s “Evening Song”—created by the current company, including its artistic directors, and featuring a sound score by Jad Abumrad and costumes by Valerie St. Pierre Smith —involve the manipulation of an expansive length of tie-dyed fabric to variously frame Hannah Klinkman and Ms. Feliz, casually clad in bright colors. Derion Loman, Zach Weiss,</p> Mr. Ellis and Mr. Buchsbaum, dressed somewhat like gladiators, act like the women&#39;s puppeteers.<p></p><p> “The Ballad,” another New York premiere on Program A, has the feel of a lecture. Darlene Kascak of the Schaghticoke Tribal Nation, who receives storytelling credit, provides voice-over narration about the mistreatment of indigenous children. Despite group movements from the quartet of men attending Ms. Feliz as a central figure, accompanied by Ben Sollee&#39;s soundscape and props by Yannick Godts, this “Ballad” remains more tale recited than tale embodied.</p><p> “Awaken Heart,” the New York premiere on Program B, and its weakest work, recycles recognizable Pilobolus configurations of lifts and knots of bodies to little more than passing effect.</p><p> The season&#39;s final week will mark, on July 28, the 100th engagement of the “Big Five-Oh!” tour. With a half-century on the boards, even its less notable efforts have helped Pilobolus sustain its popularity and provide momentum for its future.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> -先生。 Greskovic writes about dance for the Journal.</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 21:26:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/pilobolus-review-the-dance-theater-troupes-big-five-oh-69dc2f93</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/pilobolus-review-the-dance-theater-troupes-big-five-oh-69dc2f93<category>艺术评论</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Dance/Ballet</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>剧院</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>艺术回顾</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>舞蹈</category><category>芭蕾舞</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>剧院</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia’s Influence on India Wanes Even as Affection Lingers]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Though they both want to create a multipolar world, Moscow has tied itself to Beijing, New Delhi&#39;s rival. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590098381737420848"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590098381737420848"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sadanand-dhume"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BS066_dhume__AM_20180912123410.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sadanand-dhume" itemprop="url" rel="author">Sadanand Dhume</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 20, 2023 5:03 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-influence-on-india-wanes-even-as-affection-lingers-china-weapons-trade-putin-b4af1bc8"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820344?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Vladimir Putin in Moscow, July 19.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Alexander Kazakov/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Will India&#39;s longstanding love affair with Russia ever end? At first glance, the odds appear slim. Despite drawing closer to Washington over the past two decades, New Delhi has maintained tight diplomatic and military ties with Moscow. But Russia&#39;s and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/vladimir-putin">Vladimir Putin</a> &#39;s popularity among Indians won&#39;t prevent Moscow&#39;s star from fading. The rapid rise of China, combined with Russia&#39;s relative economic and technological backwardness, all but ensures that India-Russia ties will diminish over time.</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> A recent Pew survey of 24 countries found that 57% of Indians view Russia either somewhat favorably or very favorably, the highest proportion in all countries surveyed. And 59% of Indians are confident that Mr. Putin would “do the right thing regarding world affairs.” (In the US, that figure is 7%.) Russia&#39;s invasion of Ukraine last year doesn&#39;t appear to have hurt Mr. Putin&#39;s standing in India. The proportion of Indians expressing confidence in the Russian strongman rose 17 points compared with a similar survey in 2019.</p><p> India has steadfastly refused to condemn the Russian invasion. Instead, India has taken advantage of discounts, dramatically increasing purchases of Russian oil. Before the invasion, Russia accounted for around 2% of India&#39;s oil imports. In May, India imported 40% of its oil from Russia, nearly 2 million barrels a day. And for India, the world&#39;s largest importer of weapons, Russia remains its top arms supplier, providing the bulk of its strike force capability as well as technology for cruise missiles and nuclear-powered submarines.</p><p> What explains India&#39;s affinity for Russia? Both countries have long sought to create a multipolar world to replace the unipolar one that emerged after America&#39;s triumph in the Cold War. Indian Foreign Minister Subrahmanyam Jaishankar explained New Delhi&#39;s view in a recent interview with the Economist. Eurasia houses three big powers: Russia, China and India. “It&#39;s been a cardinal principle of our foreign policy, which still remains valid, that maintaining a strong relationship and a good relationship with Russia is essential,” he said.</p><p> Russia also benefits from close ties it built with India during the Cold War. Indians still remember the Soviet Union using its United Nations Security Council veto to back India on Kashmir, as well as Russia&#39;s support during the 1971 war with Pakistan, which led to the birth of Bangladesh. Indians with an anti-American attitude admire Mr. Putin for standing up to the West. For its part, Russia has used its relatively advanced military industry—and competitive prices—to lock India into long-term dependence for technology that Indians say they can&#39;t get elsewhere. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> Read More East Is East</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/identity-politics-scientific-edge-china-affirmative-action-medicine-technology-ai-supreme-court-369fe99f?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Identity Politics Could Kill America&#39;s Scientific Edge</a> <span class="date">July 6, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/can-america-rely-on-modis-india-state-visit-china-economic-gap-unrest-e5498a31?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Can America Rely on Modi&#39;s India?</a> <span class="date">2023 年 6 月 22 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/democrats-cant-count-on-asian-american-voters-republican-indian-vietnamese-chinese-aei-education-bill-clinton-bob-dole-9dcc6bb1?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">Democrats Can&#39;t Count on Asian-American Voters</a> <span class="date">June 8, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> But it is clear that Moscow&#39;s influence in India has declined dramatically—and will continue to decline. Fifty years ago, India had a planned economy and relied overwhelmingly on the Soviet Union for diplomatic support and military hardware. Committed communists and communist sympathizers held senior positions in India&#39;s government. Marxist intellectuals dominated its universities and media, and communist parties were a force in electoral politics. The KGB station in New Delhi was among the largest in the world. Soviet publishers cranked out cheap books to woo the Indian middle class.</p><p> Today, virtually nobody in India has even heard of the Russian nationalist philosopher Alexander Dugin, and Indian elites probably care more about Kim Kardashian than Karl Marx. Unlike during the Cold War, hardly anyone in India studies Russian. As the Indian security expert Happymon Jacob pointed out in Foreign Affairs last year, before the recent spike caused by oil and fertilizer, bilateral trade between India and Russia was only $13 billion in 2021, less than 10% of US-India trade. More than 4.4 million people of Indian origin live in the US Indians in Russia number fewer than 30,000, many of whom are students who couldn&#39;t get into medical school anywhere else.</p><p> Most important, Russia&#39;s closest ally, China, is also India&#39;s biggest threat. As the Indian strategic thinker C. Raja Mohan pointed out in a recent column, in the 1990s India sought a multipolar world, but today it faces the more urgent challenge of creating a multipolar Asia to stop the region from becoming China&#39;s backyard. Only America can help India with critical technologies like artificial intelligence and quantum computing. And India can no longer rely on Russian weapons and diplomatic support in its confrontation with China along the disputed Himalayan frontier. According to Stockholm International Peace Research Institute data, between 2012 and 2022 Russian arms as a proportion of India&#39;s weapons imports fell by 65%. The proportion sourced from the US, France and Israel over the same period grew 288%.</p><p> India-Russia ties survived the end of the Cold War because it made sense for both countries, but flailing in Ukraine and drawing ever closer to Beijing has made Moscow a much less attractive partner for New Delhi. As Mr. Jacob wrote, “When Indians think of their strategic partnerships, Russia is referred to in the past tense and the United States in the future.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=87D9068E-77D8-4079-9F23-679C8A6B3081&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Frussias-influence-on-india-wanes-even-as-affection-lingers-china-weapons-trade-putin-b4af1bc8&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> House Republicans passed the National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA) on July 14, after a debate that highlighted military priorities versus cultural issues. Images: Getty Images Composite: Mark Kelly <span class="imageCredit">The Wall Street Journal Interactive Edition</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 21:03:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-influence-on-india-wanes-even-as-affection-lingers-china-weapons-trade-putin-b4af1bc8</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-influence-on-india-wanes-even-as-affection-lingers-china-weapons-trade-putin-b4af1bc8<author><![CDATA[Sadanand Dhume]]></author><category> india</category><category> russia</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>美国</category><category>alliance</category><category>中国</category><category>冷战</category><category>eurasia</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Celebrities</category><category> International Relations</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>弗拉基米尔普京</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>名人</category><category>国际关系</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Post-Covid Spending Spree’s Stealthy Economic Stimulus]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> As the Fed tries to lower inflation, the industrial policies and programs of Bidenomics pump up GDP. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590098192459696832"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB10950590414055573352804590098192459696832"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Mickey D. Levy</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 20, 2023 4:58 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-stealthy-economic-stimulus-of-the-post-covid-spending-spree-fed-powell-6d171f94"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820269?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The Federal Reserve Building in Washington.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Win McNamee/Reuters</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> As the Federal Reserve ponders more rate increases to lower inflation, it faces a misunderstood counterbalance: fiscal policy that is stimulating economic growth, employment and wages. This stimulus isn&#39;t captured by mainstream Keynesian measures based on deficits and the ratio of deficits to gross domestic product. Given declines in those gauges following the Covid splurge, Fed Chairman Jerome Powell in public statements has echoed the standard assessment that fiscal policy had become restrictive to growth.</p><p> Yet this assessment based on deficit measures is misleading and ignores the measurably stimulative effects of the Biden administration&#39;s post-Covid legislation. The Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act of 2021 authorized $1 trillion of government investment over 10 years. The Chips and Science Act of 2022 authorized $278 billion on energy projects, including highly stimulative tax credits. The misnamed Inflation Reduction Act is providing $499 billion in tax credits and other subsidies. The Energy Department&#39;s heavily subsidized loan guarantees are spurring big increases in private business investment.</p><p> Together, these initiatives represent one of the largest government spending programs directed at the nation&#39;s infrastructure and industry since the 1930s. The goals include bolstering manufacturing, shifting production and consumption toward renewable energy, creating jobs that pay well, and expanding government&#39;s role in the economy.</p><p> History shows that the government has a relatively poor track record of picking productivity-enhancing projects compared with market-determined private-sector investments. It&#39;s too early to assess whether President Biden&#39;s industrial policies will lift productivity or improve standards of living relative to their costs. What is clear is that they are currently stimulating economic growth.</p><p> Standard deficit-based measures of fiscal policy capture the flows of government spending and tax receipts, but don&#39;t reflect the allocative and economic effects of these programs. Yet that&#39;s what fiscal policies do. They allocate and redistribute national resources, influencing economic behavior and outcomes.</p><p> Mr. Biden&#39;s legislation authorizes spending for as long as 10 years, and the spending and stimulus are ramping up. Accordingly, their economic effects shouldn&#39;t be considered transitory. Unlike the government&#39;s Covid income-support checks and other transfer payments that are counted in GDP only when they are spent, the US Bureau of Economic Analysis considers almost all spending for the Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act and Chips Act as government purchases that “absorb” national resources and thus counts them directly in GDP. Since mid-2022, increases in government purchases have constituted roughly 20% of the rise in GDP. Government investment generates fiscal multipliers significantly higher than multipliers on transfer payments, underlining the current stimulus.</p><p> With the 2024 presidential election looming, the Biden administration has a political incentive to step up spending under the Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act on projects like improving roads and building bridges that also create high-paying union jobs.</p><p> The Chips and Science Act focuses on scientific research and development of technologies the administration deems critical to the US It allocates $52.7 billion in spending and tax credits to chip manufacturing. Its 25% tax credits have sparked a building boom in chip-making facilities and electrical power and energy projects. This has contributed to a 2.9% increase in business fixed investment over the past four quarters even as the Fed raised rates by 5 percentage points. Continuing increases in government and private investment for the infrastructure law, Chips and Inflation Reduction Act subsidies and government loans may continue to provide a powerful buffer against tighter monetary policy.</p><p> Meanwhile, a portion of the federal government&#39;s $5 trillion in Covid spending continues to flow into the economy. While households have spent most of their savings cushions, state and local governments saved almost all the $500 billion they received in federal grants. Their holdings of US Treasury securities have surged to $1.55 trillion from their pre-pandemic average of $775 billion. As state and local governments spend their excess savings, economic activity will be stimulated long after federal deficits are recorded.</p><p> Ending the moratorium on federal student loans means roughly 20 million borrowers will have to resume servicing their loans. The moratorium has been costing the federal government about $5 billion a month. But the hit to borrowers&#39; spending will be more than offset by cost-of-living adjustments to entitlement programs. The 8.7% cost-of-living adjustment for Social Security is adding more than $100 billion to nominal disposable income in 2023. Cost-of-living adjustments for all entitlement spending programs are adding about $250 billion. This contributes to the 4% increase in real disposable income in the past year that is supporting consumer spending.</p><p> After failing to predict the economic and inflationary effects of the unprecedented $5 trillion in Covid spending, the Fed must properly assess current fiscal policies. Continuing fiscal stimulus requires the Fed to raise rates further to achieve its 2% inflation target.</p><p> <em>Mr. Levy is senior economist at Berenberg Capital Markets and a visiting scholar at the Hoover Institution.</em> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=FB987E80-FC3E-4E48-A9FD-2FE0ACE8A1C8&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fthe-stealthy-economic-stimulus-of-the-post-covid-spending-spree-fed-powell-6d171f94&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Wonder Land: Republican presidential hopefuls Ron DeSantis, Mike Pence, Nikki Haley, Tim Scott, Chris Christie, Vivek Ramaswamy and maybe even Donald Trump are united on spending. All offer a much safer future than the alternative. Images: Reuters/Zuma Press Composite: Mark Kelly <span class="imageCredit">The Wall Street Journal Interactive Edition</span></p></div></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 20:58:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-stealthy-economic-stimulus-of-the-post-covid-spending-spree-fed-powell-6d171f94</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-stealthy-economic-stimulus-of-the-post-covid-spending-spree-fed-powell-6d171f94<category> stimulus</category><category> economic policy</category><category> fiscal policy</category><category> chips act</category><category> inflation reduction act</category><category>筹码</category><category>道路</category><category>桥梁</category><category>consumer spending</category><category>美联储</category><category>disposable income</category><category> Economic Performance/Indicators</category><category> Economic Growth/Recession</category><category> Inflation Figures/Price Indices</category><category> Monetary Policy</category><category> Government Finance</category><category> Government Budget/Taxation</category><category> Economic News</category><category>政治/一般新闻</ca